{"id":831,"date":"2015-11-10T11:00:16","date_gmt":"2015-11-10T16:00:16","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/?p=831"},"modified":"2017-05-23T12:36:48","modified_gmt":"2017-05-23T16:36:48","slug":"new-guide-to-bees-of-the-great-lakes","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/new-guide-to-bees-of-the-great-lakes\/","title":{"rendered":"New Guide to Bees of the Great Lakes"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fcbkbttn_buttons_block\" id=\"fcbkbttn_left\"><\/div><p><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/new-guide-to-bees-of-the-great-lakes\/bulletin-e3282-2\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-832\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-832\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Bulletin-E3282-2.jpg\" alt=\"Bulletin-E3282-2\" width=\"797\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Bulletin-E3282-2.jpg 797w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Bulletin-E3282-2-300x141.jpg 300w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Bulletin-E3282-2-768x360.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 797px) 100vw, 797px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Project ICP researchers Dr. Jason Gibbs and Dr. Rufus Isaacs (Michigan State University) have published <a href=\"http:\/\/shop.msu.edu\/product_p\/bulletin-e3282.htm\">a new guide to the bees of the Great Lakes region and the wildflowers that support them<\/a>. The\u00a0pocket-sized guide is\u00a0designed to\u00a0help farmers and gardeners identify the many species of bees inhabiting Michigan and the rest of the Great Lakes region. The guide also provides\u00a0information on the\u00a0preferred growing conditions, flower characteristics, attractiveness to pollinators,\u00a0and best companion plants for specific native plants that can be used in farms, gardens and urban landscapes to help conserve diverse Great Lakes bee communities.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Project ICP researchers Dr. Jason